    "summary": "Repair contributor PR #95113 in place. Keep the memory-core sidecar cleanup fix narrow, address the latest hydrated check failures, and validate the edited branch before merge preflight.",
    "pr_title": "fix(memory): keep cleaning reindex sidecars after lock errors",
    "pr_body": "## What Problem This Solves\nRefs #78640 and repairs #95113 in place. The database-first memory reindex path from #94646 already removed the old full-file rename path, but cleanup of `.memory-reindex-*` shadow SQLite files should keep attempting all known sidecars after one removal fails and then report the first error.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\nThe contributor branch is narrow and editable, but the latest hydrated checks show relevant failures (`check-lint`, `checks-node-core-tooling`, and `check-additional-extension-bundled`). Repair should keep the implementation in `extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager-db.ts`, preserve the existing cleanup ownership, and keep regression proof in `extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager-db.test.ts`.\n\n## User Impact\nWindows and other lock-prone filesystems get more reliable cleanup of crash-left memory reindex sidecars without masking the original filesystem error.\n\n## Evidence\n- Current main: 5ccfc97b319ee627bd84710ceb4cd1f81b0088f0\n- Source PR: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/95113 by @849261680\n- Focused validation: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager-db.test.ts`\n- Required gate: `pnpm check:changed`\n- After repair, run a fresh Codex /review and only merge if the guarded merge preflight is clean.",
    "likely_files": [
      "extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager-db.ts",
      "extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager-db.test.ts"
    ],
    "validation_commands": [
      "node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager-db.test.ts",
      "pnpm check:changed"
    ],
